{
  "title": "M21-1, Part VIII, Subpart i, Chapter 3, Section E - Authorization Issues",
  "url": "https://www.knowva.ebenefits.va.gov/system/templates/selfservice/va_ssnew/help/customer/locale/en-US/portal/554400000001018/content/554400000177433/M21-1-Part-VIII-Subpart-i-Chapter-3-Section-E-Authorization-Issues",
  "content": "<-- Previous Section\nNext Section -->\nOverview\nIn This Section\nThis section contains the following topics:\nTopic\nTopic Name\n1\nEffective Date for Reductions and Terminations\n2\nProcessing Awards and Denials\n1\n.\nEffective Date for Reductions and Terminations\nIntroduction\nThis topic contains information on the effective date for Chapter 18 benefits, including\nreduction of Chapter 18 benefits\n, and\ntermination of Chapter 18 benefits\n.\nChange Date\nMay 14, 2015\nVIII.i.3.E.1.a\n.\nEffective Date for Reduction of Chapter 18 Benefits\nWhenever it is necessary to reduce, or discontinue a monthly allowance, generally reduce or discontinue based on the facts found, except as provided in\n38 CFR 3.105(g)\n, and\n38 CFR 3.114(b)\n.\nThe table below provides information to determine the correct effective date of a reduction or discontinuation.\nIf benefits were paid erroneously due to ...\nThen the effective date of the reduction or discontinuation is the date of ...\nbeneficiary error\nthe erroneous award.\nVA administrative error\nlast payment.\nReference\n:  For more information on resumption of discontinued benefits under\n38 U.S.C. Chapter 18\n, see\n38 CFR 3.158\n.\nVIII.i.3.E.1.b\n.\nEffective Date for Termination of Chapter 18 Benefits\nIn the event of death, discontinue Chapter 18 benefits on the last day of the month\nbefore\nthe month in which the child died.\nNote\n:  Handle abandoned claims for Chapter 18 benefits in the same manner as for compensation, pension, or Dependency and Indemnity Compensation.\nReference\n:  For more information on the effective date for termination of benefits, see\n38 CFR 3.503(b)\n.\n2\n.\nProcessing Awards and Denials\nIntroduction\nThis topic contains information on processing awards and denials of Chapter 18 monetary allowances, including\ndescription of the final stage in the Chapter 18 claims process\nroles and responsibilities for processing Chapter 18 awards and denials\n, and\naward and denial process for Chapter 18 claims\n.\nChange Date\nDecember 31, 2019\nVIII.i.3.E.2.a\n.\nDescription of the Final Stage in the Chapter 18 Claims Process\nThe final stage in the Chapter 18 claims process is to promulgate the rating decision or prepare an administrative denial and notify the claimant of the decision.\nVIII.i.3.E.2.b\n.\nRoles and Responsibilities for Processing Chapter 18 Awards and Denials\nThe authorization activity is responsible for processing awards and denials.\nVIII.i.3.E.2.c\n.\nAward and Denial Process for Chapter 18 Claims\nThe processing of Chapter 18 awards is presently accomplished using the Veterans Benefits Management System.\n<-- Previous Section\nNext Section -->\nTo Top",
